Subject: [PATCH AP-10] vmmon/vmnet: replace strncpy with strscpy (kernel >= 6.8)

Linux 6.8 added deprecation warnings for strncpy() under W=1 (and the kernel
now defaults to enabling these warnings during module builds). While not an
immediate build error, strncpy() deprecation warnings clutter the build output
and may become errors in future kernels.

strscpy() is a safe drop-in replacement for the common usage pattern of
strncpy(dst, src, sizeof(dst)): it copies at most N-1 bytes, guarantees
NUL-termination, and does not pad the remainder of the destination buffer
(unlike strncpy). This makes strscpy() strictly better for kernel module code.

The script scans all .c files in vmmon-only/ and vmnet-only/ for strncpy()
calls and replaces them with strscpy(). This patch shows the affected file
found in the community 6.16.x overlay:

  vmnet-only/vnet.h:354  strncpy(info.ctl_name, ...) → strscpy(...)

Applied by: _autopatch_strncpy_to_strscpy() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  kernel >= 6.8

---
 vmnet-only/vnet.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/vmnet-only/vnet.h b/vmnet-only/vnet.h
--- a/vmnet-only/vnet.h
+++ b/vmnet-only/vnet.h
@@ -351,7 +351,7 @@ vnet_log_ctlinfo(const char *prefix, const VNetPort *port)
    VNetPortInterface info;
    VNetPort_GetPortInterface(port, &info);
    LOG(4, (KERN_DEBUG "%s: name=%s flags=0x%x bridge=%d\n", prefix, info.name, info.flags, info.bridge));
-   strncpy(info.ctl_name, VMNET_KEXT_NAME, sizeof info.ctl_name);
+   strscpy(info.ctl_name, VMNET_KEXT_NAME, sizeof info.ctl_name);
    info.id = port->id;
